<TEXT>
The German federal government, facing sagging revenues and soaring
unemployment costs, will try to trim about DM20bn (Dollars 12.2bn) from its
1994 budget, government sources said yesterday, AP-DJ reports from Bonn.
German Finance Minister Theo Waigel announced over the weekend his intention
